      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-cou1-rqoi-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Relevance of QoIs acceptance criteria",
        "description": "QoIs used in validation (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) must map directly to the design-critical failure modes identified in the risk analysis (fatigue initiation, permanent deformation) and to the regulatory submission QoIs. Achieved: all three QoIs are explicitly listed in the 510(k) submission and in the design FMEA as primary acceptance metrics."
      },
      "rationale": "The three QoIs — construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement — are directly linked to the pedicle screw design FMEA failure modes (construct yielding, fatigue crack initiation) and are the same metrics required by the FDA 510(k) submission. No surrogate or proxy QoIs are used."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-rva",
