        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Relevance of validation activities acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The validation test configuration must replicate the COU geometry, material, loading mode, and scale without surrogate substitution. Achieved: production-representative non-cannulated 7.5 mm screws tested under the exact ASTM F1717 protocol that defines the COU; no geometric or material surrogates used.",
        "description2": "The validation activity IS the COU: the FEA model is validated directly against the ASTM F1717 test it is intended to predict."
